release: 5.5.0
tags: $:/tags/ChangeNote
title: $:/changenotes/5.5.0/#9751
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

* [[ButtonWidget]] and [[RevealWidget]] accept a new `validValues` attribute holding a filter expression; when the current state value is not among the filter results, the widget falls back to its `default`
* The `tabs` macro passes its tab list as `validValues` automatically, so removing a tab whose state tiddler still names it no longer leaves a blank panel without a selected button (fixes [[Issue #6548|https://github.com/TiddlyWiki/TiddlyWiki5/issues/6548]])
